    "description": "Are you an experienced&nbsp;<strong>Maintenance Operative?<br></strong><br>Are you interested in an opportunity in <strong>Edinburgh?<br></strong><br>Recruitment Direct UK Ltd is a premier recruiter operating across the UK and we act for our client operating across Scotland in the Construction Industry.<br>You will carry out basic routine planned preventative maintenance (PPM) and repair tasks. You will support the Area Estates team. This will be carried out to pre-set timescales, technical direction and standards.<br><br><strong>Responsibilities:</strong><br> <ul> <li>Undertake routine work such as minor repair tasks on electrical, plumbing, building equipment and painting work.</li> <li>Supported by the engineering team, you will carry out allocated tasks and be trained in electrical appliance testing, inspecting fire systems, equipment maintenance testing and inspection.</li> <li>Maintaining a safe and healthy working environment and reporting any dangers/deficiencies.</li> <li>You may be asked to work out with your normal working hours as part of the maintenance on-call rota.</li> <li>Assisting with the escorting of specialist external contractors when required</li> </ul> <br><br><strong>Candidates must be able to provide the following<br>documentation/Certifications:</strong><br> <ul> <li><strong>Minimum of 2 Standard Grades at level 3 or equivalent</strong></li> <li><strong>Enhanced Disclosure Scotland ( If not already held, must be able to make an application upon a successful interview)</strong></li> </ul>",
